  "texts": [
    "In the blind test of response prediction of unknown drugs, we divide the dataset by constraining the existence of drugs exclusively in training, validation, or testing set.",
    "Specifically, out of 223 drugs in total, 167 drugs' response data are used for a 3-fold cross-validation, and response data of 56 drugs are preserved for testing.",
    "The blind prediction task aims at testing whether the model developed on known drugs has the generalizability to predict responses of unknown drugs.",
    "In the blind test experiment, we compare our method with tCNN, GraphDRP and TGSA.",
    "DeepCDR is ignored since the code to flexibly divide the dataset according to drug occurrence is not provided."
  ],
